Hi, Ellen.
Hi, Christine.

04:22.889 --> 04:24.306
How are you doing?
Good.

04:24.307 --> 04:25.474
Where's Mommy?

04:25.475 --> 04:27.893
Mom? She's in
the bathroom.

04:27.894 --> 04:29.436
Ellen, I got you a present.

04:29.437 --> 04:31.938
You want to see
what it is?
Yeah, yeah.

04:31.939 --> 04:33.273
[ELLEN EXCLAIMS]

04:33.274 --> 04:34.900
Do you like it?
Uh-huh.

04:34.901 --> 04:37.862
Okay. Come on,
let's go find Mommy.

04:39.614 --> 04:41.239
WOMAN 1: So then
she's taking me to have...

04:41.240 --> 04:43.910
WOMAN 2: She's pregnant,
she's going to give birth.

04:52.668 --> 04:55.212
Hiya, Chuck.
How are you?
Good to see you.

04:55.213 --> 04:57.255
You gonna
make it Friday?
Friday, I'm there.

04:57.256 --> 04:58.715
We need you, pal.
We're in the cellar.

04:58.716 --> 05:00.133
You know that. Okay.
Okay.

05:00.134 --> 05:01.468
BETH: Dan, is my hair okay?

05:01.469 --> 05:03.178
You look great.
I'm serious.

05:03.179 --> 05:05.931
You're the prettiest woman
in the room, sweetheart.

05:05.932 --> 05:07.057
You liar.

05:07.058 --> 05:09.685
Dan! Danny!

05:12.188 --> 05:14.147
Hiya, Bob. How are you?

05:14.148 --> 05:15.607
Glad you could make it, Dan.

05:15.608 --> 05:17.108
Listen, I'm sorry
about the meeting tomorrow.

05:17.109 --> 05:19.653
I know it's a Saturday,
but we've got
a real crisis here.

05:19.654 --> 05:21.780
Oh, no, I understand.
You know my wife Beth?
Bob Drimmer.

05:21.781 --> 05:23.490
Pleased to meet you.
Nice to meet you.

05:23.491 --> 05:24.575
I hope you like sushi.

05:24.576 --> 05:26.284
Thank you.
I love it, Bob. Love it.

05:26.285 --> 05:27.577
What did he do to his neck?

05:27.578 --> 05:29.329
He was screwing his wife.

05:29.330 --> 05:30.747
Are you serious?
Am I serious?

05:30.748 --> 05:32.541
JIMMY: Absolutely,
you should see his wife.

05:32.542 --> 05:34.209
They had to take her
out on a stretcher.

05:34.210 --> 05:35.418
Hi, darling.

05:35.419 --> 05:36.295
You guys are bad.

05:36.296 --> 05:38.463
Who wants champagne?
Champagne?
Let's go.

05:38.464 --> 05:40.549
Champagne for everyone.
Hemlock! With a twist.

05:40.550 --> 05:44.095
DAN: Four champagnes
over here. Excuse me.
Hi.

05:46.931 --> 05:48.723
Thank you.
JIMMY: Thank you.

05:48.724 --> 05:50.100
Thank you very much.

05:50.101 --> 05:51.435
Excuse me.

05:51.769 --> 05:55.731
Jesus! Thank you. Fuck.

05:55.857 --> 05:57.732
Thank you.
No, thank you.

05:57.733 --> 06:01.027
So, what great cultural
event are we here
to celebrate tonight?

06:01.028 --> 06:02.487
Some exercise manual.

06:02.488 --> 06:04.156
Not another one?

06:04.740 --> 06:06.157
This one's different.

06:06.158 --> 06:09.203
Based on ancient
samurai discipline.

06:10.872 --> 06:14.833
Danny, look at this
guy nod. What is that,
part of the ritual?

06:14.834 --> 06:17.253
[SHUSHING] Hey...

06:18.796 --> 06:20.590
Hi, there.

06:24.260 --> 06:26.094
Jesus, if looks could kill...

06:26.095 --> 06:27.929
Glad to see you haven't
lost your touch.

06:27.930 --> 06:29.222
I think she likes me.
You do, huh?

06:29.223 --> 06:31.516
I think she wants me.
I think you're
batting zero for two,

06:31.517 --> 06:32.602
and I don't want to know you.

06:32.603 --> 06:33.894
She was undressing
me with her eyes.

06:33.895 --> 06:35.145
You think so?
Good luck, pal.

06:35.146 --> 06:37.565
She had trouble
with the buttons.

06:38.941 --> 06:41.235
WOMAN: A signed copy.

06:50.912 --> 06:53.748
Here you are, ma'am.
Oh, thank you, dear.

06:56.626 --> 06:58.335
Can I get a champagne, please?

06:58.336 --> 07:00.046
BARTENDER: You got it.

07:05.343 --> 07:08.887
I'm not saying anything.
I'm not even gonna look.

07:08.888 --> 07:10.263
Was it that bad?

07:10.264 --> 07:11.681
Let's just say I
was glad I wasn't

07:11.682 --> 07:13.308
on the receiving
end of that one.

07:13.309 --> 07:14.310
Cheers.

07:14.311 --> 07:16.770
Just gotta hate it
when guys think they can
come on like that.

07:16.771 --> 07:21.651
Jimmy's okay. He's
just a little insecure,
like the rest of us.

07:23.861 --> 07:26.029
My name is Dan Gallagher.

07:26.030 --> 07:27.405
Alex Forrest.

07:27.406 --> 07:29.866
Nice to meet you.
What is your connection here?

07:29.867 --> 07:32.661
I'm an editor at Robbins & Hart. And you?

07:32.662 --> 07:36.456
I'm with Miller,
Goodman and Hurst.
I do all your legal work.

07:36.457 --> 07:38.583
I haven't seen you
around their office, though.

07:38.584 --> 07:42.088
I've just been with them
a couple of weeks.

07:50.137 --> 07:51.262
I have to go.

07:51.263 --> 07:53.641
Is that your wife?
Yeah.

07:53.933 --> 07:55.725
Better run along.

07:55.726 --> 07:58.229
It was very nice to meet you.

08:03.651 --> 08:05.443
"Make concessions
with your body."

08:05.444 --> 08:07.570
What does this mean,
"make concessions"?

08:07.571 --> 08:09.489
Oh, give me a break.
Give you a break?

08:09.490 --> 08:11.534
What does this mean?

08:11.784 --> 08:14.036
How many did you buy, huh?

08:22.712 --> 08:24.170
BETH: Well,
thanks again, Christine.

08:24.171 --> 08:25.630
CHRISTINE: Any time, Mrs.
Gallagher.

08:25.631 --> 08:26.923
BETH: Good night.

08:26.924 --> 08:28.259
[DOOR CLOSING]

08:35.515 --> 08:38.394
Aren't you forgetting something?

08:44.775 --> 08:46.402
[SIGHS]

08:49.113 --> 08:50.698
Quincy, let's hit it, pal.

08:59.206 --> 09:01.917
You're such a good boy, yes.

09:04.253 --> 09:08.298
You did such good business.
You did good business.

09:08.299 --> 09:09.632
You're the best boy.

09:09.633 --> 09:11.343
Good night.

09:19.810 --> 09:22.480
It's just for tonight, honey.

09:24.315 --> 09:27.817
When you first see
the house, don't show
any interest at all,

09:27.818 --> 09:29.402
otherwise we can't negotiate.

09:29.403 --> 09:30.737
Will you stop worrying about it?

09:30.738 --> 09:32.864
Ellen, are you
chewing gum again?
What's to worry, though?

09:32.865 --> 09:34.574
We can't afford it anymore.

09:34.575 --> 09:36.242
Daddy, is Granny
going to be there?

09:36.243 --> 09:37.827
Just up the road
from Mom and Dad.
Yes.

09:37.828 --> 09:39.579
Which is another
reason not to buy it.

09:39.580 --> 09:40.789
I didn't hear that.

09:40.790 --> 09:43.249
What's to worry about?
Can't afford the
goddamn thing, anyway.

09:43.250 --> 09:46.420
BETH: Oh, come on.
Hold on to him, honey.

09:48.422 --> 09:50.256
Let's just not
worry about it, okay?

09:50.257 --> 09:52.258
I haven't even seen
the damn place yet.

09:52.259 --> 09:54.512
I may not even like it.

09:54.804 --> 09:58.057
Ellen? The gum?
Thank you.

10:00.601 --> 10:02.227
ELLEN: Come on, Quincy.
Come on, boy.

10:02.228 --> 10:04.312
No, honey.
Quincy's got to stay
here with Daddy.

10:04.313 --> 10:05.814
Daddy's gonna be all alone.

10:05.815 --> 10:08.900
Sorry, Quincy.
Now, you're not gonna
forget to walk him, are you?

10:08.901 --> 10:10.276
I promise.
You promise.

10:10.277 --> 10:12.612
Okay. You have
a good meeting.

10:12.613 --> 10:14.155
Okay. See you
tomorrow night.

10:14.156 --> 10:15.616
Love you.

10:36.303 --> 10:40.224
MAN: Two times down,
third time up,
he looked like a jellyfish.

10:42.351 --> 10:45.479
Hi, Bob.
Hi, Dan. Sorry to
ruin your weekend.

10:45.521 --> 10:47.147
Please, give my apologies
to your lovely wife.

10:47.148 --> 10:49.900
David, hi.
BOB: Help yourself.

10:50.651 --> 10:52.569
So, how are you
feeling?
Don't ask.

10:52.570 --> 10:56.447
Henry's out of town,
so I asked Alex Forrest
to stand in for him.

10:56.448 --> 10:59.659
Anybody know where she is?
WOMAN: She's on her way.

10:59.660 --> 11:01.244
Well, since we've
got a little time,

11:01.245 --> 11:04.205
maybe you can tell us
exactly what happened
to your neck, Bob.

11:04.206 --> 11:06.542
[ALL LAUGHING]

11:07.251 --> 11:09.252
That's cute. Very cute.

11:09.253 --> 11:11.212
Sorry I'm late.
I was getting the file.

11:11.213 --> 11:13.840
Dan, this is Alex Forrest,
our new associate editor.

11:13.841 --> 11:15.717
We've met before. Hi.
Yeah, hello.

11:15.718 --> 11:17.760
Okay. Can we get
started, Dan?

11:17.761 --> 11:19.930
Okay, here's the story.

11:20.097 --> 11:23.099
You want to publish a novel
in which one of the characters

11:23.100 --> 11:26.020
is a senator from New Jersey
who's fooling around.

11:26.312 --> 11:28.396
Now,
there's a certain congressman
from Ohio

11:28.397 --> 11:30.064
who claims the character's
based upon him,

11:30.065 --> 11:32.567
and he's filed an injunction
against the publication.

11:32.568 --> 11:35.361
Look, the congressman's bald.
This guy has hair.

11:35.362 --> 11:36.821
They're from different states,
for Christ's sake.

11:36.822 --> 11:38.740
Look, if we don't
sell those books,
we're screwed.

11:38.741 --> 11:41.159
Well, that's all fine,
but if I'm gonna go
to court to prove

11:41.160 --> 11:43.077
the senator's not based upon
this congressman,

11:43.078 --> 11:45.455
then I have to know the truth.

11:45.456 --> 11:50.752
Now... Well, strictly between
these walls, all right?

11:50.753 --> 11:54.632
Did the author have an affair
with Mr. Ohio or not?

11:59.470 --> 12:01.263
Yeah, she did.

12:01.597 --> 12:05.141
But she also had
a lot of affairs
with other politicians.

12:05.142 --> 12:07.644
Any one of them could
make the same claim.

12:07.645 --> 12:09.812
She swears this
character's fictitious.

12:09.813 --> 12:11.773
I just got off
the phone with her.

12:11.774 --> 12:13.484
And you believe her?

12:14.693 --> 12:16.779
Yeah, I believe her.

12:17.404 --> 12:19.530
BOB: Okay, now that
we've got that on the table,

12:19.531 --> 12:21.324
what can we do to
lift that injunction?

12:21.325 --> 12:23.117
If we believe the girl,
is there some way

12:23.118 --> 12:24.661
we can get to the congressman?

12:24.662 --> 12:26.537
They take
campaign contributions.

12:26.538 --> 12:28.539
Can we buy him off?
Can we frighten him off?

12:28.540 --> 12:31.459
Is there something in his past
that we can find out about?

12:31.460 --> 12:34.380
I mean, we need to
use some leverage.
I got 25...

12:48.477 --> 12:50.854
Give me a break, will you?

12:53.565 --> 12:55.192
Come on.

12:58.153 --> 12:59.780
Come on!

13:00.531 --> 13:02.032
Come on.

13:08.330 --> 13:09.873
[ALEX LAUGHING]

13:10.791 --> 13:14.711
Was it made in Taiwan?
Yeah. These are tough to find.

13:14.712 --> 13:17.381
Wait, wait. Here.
We got one.

13:19.258 --> 13:20.676
DAN: Come on!

13:22.553 --> 13:25.638
What do you say, you
want to go get a drink
till it stops?

13:25.639 --> 13:27.725
Yeah, I'd love it.
Okay.

13:27.933 --> 13:29.518
Come on.

13:30.060 --> 13:32.062
[ALEX EXCLAIMS]

13:32.938 --> 13:34.063
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

13:34.064 --> 13:36.649
DAN: The strangest
case I ever handled?

13:36.650 --> 13:40.611
Well, the truth was,
I never actually
handled a case.

13:40.612 --> 13:43.156
The strangest case
I ever came near to

13:43.157 --> 13:45.616
was when my parents
got divorced.

13:45.617 --> 13:47.618
And my mother asked me
to represent her.

13:47.619 --> 13:48.745
[BOTH LAUGHING]

13:48.746 --> 13:50.622
You're kidding?
That's what I said.

13:50.873 --> 13:52.165
"What do you mean?"
she told me.

13:52.166 --> 13:53.291
"You know what
an asshole the guy is.

13:53.292 --> 13:56.252
"You've been a witness
to this marriage for
the past 29 years."

13:56.253 --> 13:58.171
Can you believe this?
This is coming from my mother.

13:58.172 --> 14:00.798
No. How did you
get out of it?

14:00.799 --> 14:03.634
Well, you can't exactly
turn your mother down.

14:03.635 --> 14:06.679
So, I escaped on a technicality.

14:06.680 --> 14:07.889
Which was what?

14:07.890 --> 14:09.933
I didn't practice family law.

14:11.018 --> 14:14.270
And it was true, you know.
And she bought it.

14:14.271 --> 14:18.150
ALEX: You're making this up.
Could I make
something up like that?

14:19.860 --> 14:21.320
Waiter?

14:24.365 --> 14:26.908
I've got a lot of pull
here, you know.
My favorite restaurant.

14:26.909 --> 14:28.034
Yeah, I noticed.

14:28.035 --> 14:30.454
They know me well. Miss?

14:30.788 --> 14:32.121
You want coffee?
I'd love one.

14:32.122 --> 14:33.916
Can we have two coffees, please?

14:35.918 --> 14:37.043
[DAN SIGHING]

14:37.044 --> 14:38.628
Well, I tell you, it's a...

14:38.629 --> 14:40.672
Do you want one?
No, thank you.

14:42.049 --> 14:45.510
It's funny being
a lawyer, you know.
It's like being a doctor.

14:45.511 --> 14:47.804
Everybody's telling you
their innermost secrets.

14:47.805 --> 14:49.264
Oh, God.

14:49.765 --> 14:51.599
You must have to be discreet.

14:51.600 --> 14:53.310
Oh, God, yeah.

14:53.644 --> 14:55.145
Are you?

14:58.190 --> 14:59.691
Am I what?

15:01.193 --> 15:02.653
Discreet.

15:09.660 --> 15:11.662
Yes, I'm discreet.

15:13.038 --> 15:14.415
Me, too.

15:21.422 --> 15:22.922
Can I ask you something?

15:22.923 --> 15:24.173
What?

15:24.174 --> 15:25.925
Why don't you
have a date tonight?
It's Saturday night.

15:25.926 --> 15:27.927
I did have a date.

15:27.928 --> 15:31.682
I stood him up.
That was the
phone call I made.

15:34.017 --> 15:35.686
Does that make you feel good?

15:37.980 --> 15:40.315
It doesn't make me feel bad.

15:42.234 --> 15:44.528
So, where's your wife?

15:44.862 --> 15:46.738
Where's my wife?

15:48.615 --> 15:51.242
My wife is in the country
with her parents,

15:51.243 --> 15:53.620
visiting them for the weekend.

15:55.080 --> 15:57.790
And you're here
with a strange girl,
being a naughty boy.

15:57.791 --> 16:00.836
I don't think having dinner
with anybody is a crime.

16:01.670 --> 16:03.130
Not yet.

16:05.632 --> 16:07.508
Will it be?

16:07.509 --> 16:09.135
I don't know.
What do you think?

16:09.136 --> 16:12.890
I definitely think
it's going to be up to you.

16:16.226 --> 16:19.271
I can't say yet.
I haven't made up my mind.

16:23.275 --> 16:26.195
[CLEARING THROAT]
At least you're
very honest.

16:28.322 --> 16:30.323
We were attracted
to each other at the party.

16:30.324 --> 16:32.034
That was obvious.

16:33.785 --> 16:36.705
You're on your own
for the night.
That's also obvious.

16:42.377 --> 16:44.421
We're two adults.

16:51.720 --> 16:53.639
Let's get the check.

16:54.389 --> 16:56.225
[BOTH PANTING]

17:47.859 --> 17:49.528
[ALEX LAUGHING]

18:02.124 --> 18:04.501
[BOTH LAUGHING]

18:21.643 --> 18:23.353
[ALEX PANTING]

18:24.855 --> 18:26.023
[GRUNTS]

18:39.244 --> 18:41.495
Oh, that was great.

18:41.496 --> 18:43.582
Oh, thank God.
Thank God.

18:49.421 --> 18:51.882
Are you feeling energetic?

18:54.551 --> 18:56.261
What do you have in mind?

18:56.386 --> 18:58.764
[BAND PLAYING <i>SABINO]</i>

19:45.852 --> 19:49.439
DAN: How you
getting home?
I don't know, I live upstairs.

19:49.606 --> 19:52.275
This is the building?
Yeah.

19:57.614 --> 20:00.909
Well, where do I
get a cab, you know?

20:04.705 --> 20:06.289
[ALEX LAUGHING]

20:11.545 --> 20:13.295
Have you ever done
it in an elevator?

20:13.296 --> 20:15.632
Not recently, no.
I bet you haven't.

22:09.162 --> 22:10.205
[QUINCY WHIMPERS]

22:10.206 --> 22:13.166
Oh, I'm sorry, baby.
I'm sorry.

22:13.708 --> 22:15.335
How are you?

22:23.802 --> 22:26.345
BETH: Hi.
What happened to you?

22:26.346 --> 22:29.348
<i>I tried you earlier. I'm gonna go... I guess you're not back yet.</i>

22:29.349 --> 22:34.271
<i>Well, I'm gonna go to bed now, so call me in the morning.Bye-bye.</i>

22:47.701 --> 22:49.619
[PHONE RINGING]

22:52.664 --> 22:56.250
Hello? Oh, Dan, darling,
we were expecting you.

22:56.251 --> 22:57.835
DAN: I'm sorry.
I had work to do.

22:57.836 --> 22:58.670
That's a pity.

22:58.671 --> 23:00.629
We really wanted
you to see that house.

23:00.630 --> 23:02.631
<i>Well, I'll see it</i>
<i>next time.</i>
Yes, of course.

23:02.632 --> 23:03.924
You want to speak to Beth?

23:03.925 --> 23:05.384
Yes, please.

23:05.385 --> 23:06.928
JOAN: <i>Yes, all right.</i>

23:10.098 --> 23:12.934
The phone, it's Dan.
Here you are.

23:14.769 --> 23:17.480
Well, hello.
What happened to you?

23:18.857 --> 23:19.816
Hi...

23:19.817 --> 23:22.985
Nothing. I just went out
and had dinner
with Bill last night.

23:22.986 --> 23:24.487
How is he?

23:25.697 --> 23:30.409
He's... Bill's, you know...
Bill's Bill,
the same as usual.

23:30.410 --> 23:31.702
BETH: Is he still with that girl?

23:31.703 --> 23:35.205
Well, he wasn't last night.
I think it's over.

23:35.206 --> 23:37.616
He really didn't seem like
he wanted to talk about it.

23:38.585 --> 23:40.419
So, are you
getting any work done?

23:40.420 --> 23:41.463
DAN: <i>Yeah, I'm working.</i>

23:41.464 --> 23:44.506
Oh, listen, there's some
of the spaghetti sauce
in the refrigerator,

23:44.507 --> 23:45.592
if you get hungry.

23:45.593 --> 23:47.886
Great.
Okay. How's Ellen doing?

23:48.386 --> 23:52.933
She is having the best time.
I just hope that
Dad survives it.

23:53.266 --> 23:55.392
Honey, I don't know
how to tell you this.

23:55.393 --> 23:59.563
But... She wants a rabbit.

23:59.564 --> 24:01.148
DAN: <i>Beth, no rabbits.</i>

24:01.149 --> 24:04.234
Jesus Christ!
This goddamn family's
turning into Noah's Ark.

24:04.235 --> 24:08.572
I mean, please!
Give her a kiss,
all right? But no promises.

24:08.573 --> 24:09.491
All right.

24:09.491 --> 24:10.533
DAN: <i>When are you coming home?</i>

24:10.534 --> 24:12.576
Well,
it's getting complicated.
DAN: <i>Why's that?</i>

24:12.577 --> 24:14.370
There's a problem
with the house.

24:14.371 --> 24:16.164
They sold it.

24:16.790 --> 24:21.377
Very funny.
No. We can't get in to see it
until late this afternoon.

24:21.378 --> 24:22.878
I'm not up to
fighting the traffic.

24:22.879 --> 24:24.714
I thought I would
come in tomorrow.

24:25.215 --> 24:26.174
What about school?

24:26.175 --> 24:30.052
She's only 5 years old.
What's she gonna miss?
Trigonometry?

24:30.053 --> 24:31.470
Yeah, okay. All right.

24:31.471 --> 24:33.806
Well, then I'll see you
when I get home from work.

24:33.807 --> 24:36.183
Okay. See you tomorrow.

24:36.184 --> 24:39.062
Okay, thanks.
Have a good time.

24:43.191 --> 24:44.985
[PHONE RINGING]

24:46.444 --> 24:47.445
DAN: Yeah?

24:47.446 --> 24:51.700
What happened? I woke up.
You weren't here. I hate that.

24:58.581 --> 25:00.165
You didn't get my note?

25:00.166 --> 25:01.584
<i>What note?</i>

25:02.460 --> 25:05.296
I left you a note
right by your bed.

25:08.842 --> 25:10.051
Oh.

25:15.098 --> 25:19.768
That's nice.
I thought we were going
to spend the day together.

25:19.769 --> 25:23.063
Alex, look, I've got
so much work to do today.
I can't.

25:23.064 --> 25:26.233
Why don't you just come over? I'll cook us lunch.

25:26.234 --> 25:27.235
I got to take
the dog for a walk.

25:27.236 --> 25:29.445
The poor dog has
not been out of
this house all day.

25:29.446 --> 25:30.405
<i>I got to take him out.</i>

25:30.406 --> 25:35.160
Well, bring the dog.
I love animals.
I'm a great cook. Come on.

25:36.286 --> 25:38.537
Listen,
I'd love to, but I can't.
All right? I really can't.

25:38.538 --> 25:41.623
<i>Do what you have to do,
then come over afterwards.</i>

25:41.624 --> 25:43.918
<i>We can always eat late.</i>

25:45.170 --> 25:51.051
Or you can work here.
I won't disturb you,
I promise.

25:51.801 --> 25:53.470
I'll be a good girl.

25:56.181 --> 25:59.851
Yeah,
you don't give up, do you?
You just don't give up.

26:00.894 --> 26:02.312
[QUINCY PANTING]

26:04.272 --> 26:05.899
[ALEX EXCLAIMS]

26:06.232 --> 26:07.776
DAN: Come on!

26:14.741 --> 26:16.659
BOY: Come on!

26:19.454 --> 26:21.623
DAN: Quincy, no! Quincy!

26:22.457 --> 26:25.042
I got it! I got it!
He's free!

26:25.043 --> 26:30.172
Quincy, cover me. I'm on it.
Go deep. He fires. Throws...

26:30.173 --> 26:33.635
Okay.
She's got it.
Yes. It's back.

26:33.885 --> 26:36.471
Over the head. He's got it.

26:44.229 --> 26:46.189
Dan? Dan!

26:49.067 --> 26:52.362
Dan? Dan, can you hear me?

26:52.779 --> 26:54.489
Oh, my God!

27:01.788 --> 27:04.289
You bastard.
Your face!

27:04.290 --> 27:05.582
Your face!

27:05.583 --> 27:07.459
That was a shitty thing to do.

27:07.460 --> 27:09.461
I'm sorry.
I was just fooling around.

27:09.462 --> 27:12.340
My father died
of a heart attack.

27:13.925 --> 27:17.720
I was 7 years old.
It happened
right in front of me.

27:19.931 --> 27:21.807
Honey, I'm sorry.

27:21.808 --> 27:22.642
Really, I had no idea.

27:22.643 --> 27:25.436
If I did, I never
would have done
anything like that.

27:31.067 --> 27:33.528
Wait, he didn't die?
He's alive?

27:34.028 --> 27:37.532
Yeah, he's alive and well
and living in Phoenix.

27:39.742 --> 27:43.746
I guess you certainly
got me, didn't you?

27:53.464 --> 27:55.758
[OPERA MUSIC PLAYING]

28:02.724 --> 28:04.349
Let's hear it.

28:04.350 --> 28:06.185
[VOLUME INCREASES]

28:06.186 --> 28:10.648
I hope you like spaghetti.
Specialty of the house.

28:10.773 --> 28:13.109
It goes with the opera.

28:19.991 --> 28:22.243
DAN: It smells so good.

28:28.458 --> 28:30.542
Anything else
for me to do?
No, nothing.

28:30.543 --> 28:31.752
Just make yourself at home.

28:31.753 --> 28:33.378
You can change
the tape if you want to.

28:33.379 --> 28:34.796
No, this is great.

28:34.797 --> 28:37.090
I love <i>Madame Butterfly.</i>

28:37.091 --> 28:40.177
Really?
It's my favorite opera.

28:40.178 --> 28:41.303
Mine, too.

28:41.304 --> 28:44.140
It's the first opera I ever saw.

28:44.349 --> 28:48.853
My father,
he took me to the old Met.
I was 5 years old.

28:49.020 --> 28:50.229
Did it make any sense?

28:50.230 --> 28:50.855
I got most of it.

28:50.856 --> 28:56.611
There was this US sailor
setting up house with
this Japanese lady.

28:59.072 --> 29:00.530
That was all fine.

29:00.531 --> 29:04.661
But in the final act,
after he left her,

29:06.704 --> 29:10.500
my father told me,
"She's gonna kill herself."

29:11.542 --> 29:12.834
And I was terrified.

29:12.835 --> 29:16.547
I was...
I climbed right
underneath the chair.

29:18.758 --> 29:20.677
It's right here.

29:21.636 --> 29:24.055
This is it. It's right...

29:34.691 --> 29:36.234
It's funny.

29:37.777 --> 29:39.736
What?
It's one of the only times

29:39.737 --> 29:44.033
I remember my father
being nice to me when
I was a kid.

29:44.450 --> 29:47.370
Comforting me at Madame Butterfly.

30:22.905 --> 30:24.240
What?

30:26.242 --> 30:28.578
What are you thinking?

30:30.079 --> 30:32.664
I was wondering
why is it that all
the interesting guys

30:32.665 --> 30:34.292
are always married.

30:35.293 --> 30:37.085
Well, maybe that's why
you find them interesting,

30:37.086 --> 30:39.756
the fact you can't have them.

30:40.590 --> 30:43.301
How long have you been married?

30:45.136 --> 30:46.721
Nine years.

30:47.638 --> 30:49.306
Do you have any kids?

30:49.307 --> 30:51.267
I got a 6-year-old girl.

30:54.020 --> 30:55.605
Sounds good.

30:59.275 --> 31:01.152
Yeah, I'm lucky.

31:03.029 --> 31:05.573
So what are you doing here?

31:13.915 --> 31:17.334
Boy, you know how to
ask the wrong thing.

31:17.335 --> 31:19.753
No, I really want to know.

31:19.754 --> 31:23.800
I had a wonderful
time last night.
I'd like to see you again.

31:24.092 --> 31:26.135
Is that so terrible?

31:26.886 --> 31:27.986
No.

31:28.846 --> 31:32.058
I just don't think
it's possible, now.

31:35.311 --> 31:39.273
It's really strange.
I feel like I
know you already.

31:40.149 --> 31:43.152
I just want to know
where I stand.

31:46.697 --> 31:49.033
I think you're terrific.

31:52.578 --> 31:54.497
But I'm married.

31:56.916 --> 31:59.043
What can I say? I...

32:03.673 --> 32:05.341
Just my luck.

32:32.535 --> 32:33.828
Shit!

32:35.913 --> 32:38.623
What are you doing?
I gotta go.

32:38.624 --> 32:41.126
I thought you said she wasn't
coming back till tomorrow.

32:41.127 --> 32:45.882
She's not, but I got
things to do, honey.
I got to go home.

32:47.633 --> 32:50.135
You know,
I don't think I like this.

32:50.136 --> 32:52.221
Like what?

32:52.513 --> 32:56.600
The way you run away
after every time we make love.

32:56.601 --> 32:58.185
Well, Alex,
what difference
does it make

32:58.186 --> 32:59.936
whether I leave now
or in the morning?

32:59.937 --> 33:01.022
The fact is, I gotta go.

33:01.023 --> 33:02.689
Well, you're not gonna
leave now.

33:02.690 --> 33:04.608
Oh, come on.
Will you stop it?

33:04.609 --> 33:05.859
I mean it.

33:05.860 --> 33:07.570
Come on! Hey, Alex!
Come on!

33:11.324 --> 33:13.409
What's the problem?

33:14.911 --> 33:16.454
I'm sorry.

33:18.706 --> 33:21.875
Jesus Christ, I mean,
let's be reasonable.

33:21.876 --> 33:23.293
Be reasonable?

33:23.294 --> 33:24.754
[LAUGHING] What?

33:25.338 --> 33:27.589
"Thank you, goodbye.
Don't call me,
I'll call you."

33:27.590 --> 33:32.302
Look,
you knew about me, all right?
I didn't hide anything.

33:32.303 --> 33:34.262
I thought
it was understood.
What was understood?

33:34.263 --> 33:37.349
The opportunity was there,
and we took it.

33:37.350 --> 33:39.392
Come on now,
we're adults, aren't we?

33:39.393 --> 33:41.186
What's that supposed to mean?

33:41.187 --> 33:42.896
I thought we could
have a good time.

33:42.897 --> 33:44.231
No, you didn't.

33:44.232 --> 33:45.482
You thought you'd
have a good time.

33:45.483 --> 33:47.359
You didn't stop for a second
to think about me.

33:47.360 --> 33:50.237
That's crazy.
You knew the rules, Alex.

33:50.238 --> 33:51.864
What rules?

33:52.657 --> 33:55.825
Look, Alex. I like you.

33:55.826 --> 33:57.702
And if I wasn't
with somebody else,

33:57.703 --> 33:59.371
maybe I'd be with you.
But I am.

33:59.372 --> 34:03.125
Please,
don't justify yourself.
It's pathetic.

34:03.626 --> 34:07.380
If you'd tell me to fuck off,
I'd have more respect for you.

34:09.924 --> 34:12.426
All right then, fuck off.

34:13.803 --> 34:16.054
And you get out!

34:36.033 --> 34:36.784
I'm going.

34:36.784 --> 34:40.830
Why don't you come over here
and say goodbye nicely?

34:41.706 --> 34:43.623
Let's be friends.

34:56.094 --> 34:57.680
Baby, no.

34:58.472 --> 34:59.723
It's okay.

34:59.724 --> 35:00.890
[SOBBING]

35:00.891 --> 35:02.267
It's okay.

35:02.268 --> 35:04.144
Sorry if I upset you.

35:04.145 --> 35:06.355
It's okay, it's okay, really.

35:15.740 --> 35:18.367
[WHISPERING]
It's okay. All right.
That's okay.

35:19.994 --> 35:22.371
Your hands are all wet.

35:24.123 --> 35:25.041
Jesus!

35:25.042 --> 35:28.878
Jesus Christ!
Come here,
come here, come here.

35:29.211 --> 35:30.838
[ALEX CRYING]

35:31.631 --> 35:33.466
Hold on. Hold on.

35:36.510 --> 35:38.346
[ALEX EXCLAIMING]

35:42.642 --> 35:44.518
DAN Nice and tight.

36:49.208 --> 36:51.919
[DAN DIALING PHONE]

36:55.047 --> 36:58.467
DAN: Hi.
Did you just call me?

36:59.552 --> 37:02.053
I was in the shower.
I heard the phone.

37:02.054 --> 37:04.223
I thought it was you.

37:05.099 --> 37:08.477
So, how are you?
Did you have a good day?

37:09.812 --> 37:11.480
Yeah, yeah.

37:13.858 --> 37:18.403
Really? That's terrific.
That's really terrific.

37:18.404 --> 37:20.406
You sound excited.

37:23.242 --> 37:24.493
Yeah.

37:26.036 --> 37:28.246
No, I'm not against the idea,
I mean...

37:28.247 --> 37:32.042
Don't get me wrong.
It's just the money.

37:35.087 --> 37:36.422
Yeah.

37:41.218 --> 37:42.803
Yeah.

37:43.179 --> 37:46.599
Okay, darling.
I love you.

37:48.517 --> 37:49.852
Bye.

38:09.747 --> 38:11.081
Alex?

38:18.923 --> 38:21.050
How are you feeling?

38:23.719 --> 38:25.095
Okay.

38:28.224 --> 38:30.059
I gotta go.

38:31.310 --> 38:33.813
Will you call me sometime?

38:34.814 --> 38:37.106
You don't have to,
if you don't want to.

38:37.107 --> 38:38.859
No, I want to.

38:39.276 --> 38:42.530
You promise me
you're gonna go
see the doctor?

38:42.613 --> 38:43.989
Okay.

38:53.165 --> 38:54.750
Goodbye.

38:55.334 --> 38:56.752
Goodbye.

38:59.171 --> 39:00.630
You take care.

39:00.631 --> 39:02.049
You, too.

39:31.579 --> 39:33.121
Shit.

39:33.122 --> 39:36.082
Look what I got.
Look what I got for you here.

39:36.083 --> 39:38.751
A little
spaghetti and meat sauce.
That's it, buddy.

39:38.752 --> 39:42.839
We'll make
an Italian out of you yet.
That's a good boy. Good dog.

39:42.840 --> 39:45.134
Have a good one, yeah.

40:03.736 --> 40:06.487
What are you doing here?
It's 8:00 a.m.

40:06.488 --> 40:07.614
I'm in the shitter, Martha.

40:07.615 --> 40:09.782
Got to be in court by 2:00
and I'm really behind.

40:09.783 --> 40:11.826
Will you do me a favor?
Cancel everything.

40:11.827 --> 40:14.621
Then call Drimmer,
tell him we're fine.

40:14.622 --> 40:16.164
I'll be there by 2:00.

40:16.165 --> 40:17.666
At 2:00? Okay.

40:18.542 --> 40:20.794
Good morning, Martha.

40:26.884 --> 40:28.134
Daddy!

40:28.135 --> 40:29.761
Hey! Honey!
Oh, God, I missed you.

40:29.762 --> 40:30.846
We had a great time!
Yeah?

40:30.847 --> 40:32.513
I went for
a walk with Grandpa...
You did?

40:32.514 --> 40:34.057
...and we saw rabbits
and chased them...

40:34.058 --> 40:35.100
Well, good.
Why don't you slow down?

40:35.101 --> 40:36.726
I can't understand
one word you're saying.

40:36.727 --> 40:37.894
Daddy, I want a rabbit.

40:37.895 --> 40:38.938
I know you do, honey.

40:38.939 --> 40:41.690
Hi, darling.
How are you?
Good.

40:42.399 --> 40:43.692
Good.

40:49.865 --> 40:51.741
God, I missed you.

40:51.742 --> 40:53.409
[LAUGHING] Liar.

40:53.410 --> 40:54.828
I did.

40:56.872 --> 40:59.875
Well, I should go away
more often.

41:10.344 --> 41:12.387
I did this one.
DAN: You did?

41:12.388 --> 41:13.930
Yes. Pick another one.

41:13.931 --> 41:15.848
I thought it was
this row you picked.

41:15.849 --> 41:17.600
No. It was this one.

41:17.601 --> 41:19.853
I think you're in
a lot of trouble.

41:20.062 --> 41:21.563
[DAN LAUGHS]

41:26.694 --> 41:28.487
[MUMBLING]

41:38.247 --> 41:39.580
Okay.

41:39.581 --> 41:41.207
Now, pick a card, Dad.

41:41.208 --> 41:42.542
Any card at all?

41:42.543 --> 41:43.585
Mmm...

41:43.586 --> 41:45.920
Yeah?
Where'd you learn this?
Of course.

41:45.921 --> 41:48.507
Grandpa showed me.
Oh.

41:50.259 --> 41:51.885
Surprise.

41:56.724 --> 41:58.600
So how was it?

41:59.852 --> 42:03.272
Oh, come on, I'm a big boy.
I can take it.

42:04.398 --> 42:06.567
It had a place for rabbits.

42:06.734 --> 42:11.280
Oh, no! She said it.
She said the R-word.
Oh, no!

42:12.448 --> 42:15.533
Not rabbits? Rabbits?

42:15.534 --> 42:17.036
Rabbits!

42:17.745 --> 42:19.412
Rabbits!
DAN: Not rabbits?

42:19.413 --> 42:20.497
ELLEN: Rabbits!

42:20.498 --> 42:23.499
Well, what can I tell you?
It's absolutely perfect.

42:23.500 --> 42:25.251
In this row?

42:25.252 --> 42:26.711
No.

42:26.712 --> 42:30.883
So, when are you
gonna come up and
take a look at it?

42:31.258 --> 42:32.675
Just for the hell of it?

42:32.676 --> 42:34.261
ELLEN: In this row?

42:34.553 --> 42:37.139
How about tomorrow morning?

42:37.723 --> 42:39.098
ELLEN: Daddy, which row?

42:39.099 --> 42:40.434
You mean it?

42:40.851 --> 42:43.436
If you get me
back to the office
by 1:00, yeah.

42:43.437 --> 42:45.439
Which row, Dad?

42:45.898 --> 42:48.567
It's in this row, sweetheart.

43:09.546 --> 43:11.507
BETH: Oh, I love this.

43:12.716 --> 43:13.926
Dan?

43:14.635 --> 43:18.514
Honey? Honey, come here.
I want you to see this.

43:24.394 --> 43:25.687
Well?

43:25.813 --> 43:28.898
It's... It's okay.
It's okay.

43:28.899 --> 43:31.818
[GROANS]
Come on, it's fantastic!

43:31.819 --> 43:33.236
It's great. It's great.

43:33.237 --> 43:37.073
Just think of all the
money we're gonna save,
not living in New York.

43:37.074 --> 43:40.701
The local high school
is excellent. My own
children went there.

43:40.702 --> 43:42.078
You see?

43:42.079 --> 43:43.454
This is a terrific
area for kids.

43:43.455 --> 43:45.873
Oh, I'm sure. I'm sure.
Is it okay if I go upstairs?

43:45.874 --> 43:48.126
Please, go right ahead.
I'll wait for you down here.

43:48.127 --> 43:49.545
Thank you.

43:51.505 --> 43:53.756
You know,
we still got to decorate.

43:53.757 --> 43:56.509
We can fix up anything.
We can have painting parties.

43:56.510 --> 44:00.055
Painting parties?
Beth, you're making me
very nervous.

44:06.478 --> 44:09.690
Well, now, look at this.
This is fantastic.

44:11.316 --> 44:13.442
This would make
a terrific playroom.

44:13.443 --> 44:15.695
What are you talking
about, playroom?
This is my den!

44:15.696 --> 44:17.196
It's a den!

44:17.197 --> 44:20.032
BETH: I knew you
were going to like it.

44:20.033 --> 44:21.577
[BETH GIGGLES]

44:22.327 --> 44:23.745
DAN: I like it.

44:36.592 --> 44:38.426
I'll be in court.
How you doing, Dan?

44:38.427 --> 44:41.304
Hi, Eunice.
Martha back from lunch?
Good afternoon, Mr. Gallagher.

44:41.305 --> 44:42.680
She just returned.

44:42.681 --> 44:43.932
Thank you.

44:52.191 --> 44:53.400
Hi.

44:53.567 --> 44:55.026
Hello.

44:55.027 --> 44:58.779
This isn't a bad time,
is it? I was in the area.
I figured that...

44:58.780 --> 45:01.825
No, no.
You want to come
into my office?

45:12.753 --> 45:14.880
This is his account?

45:15.505 --> 45:19.217
Hey, Danny. Danny, you
gonna be in your office
a little later, there's...

45:19.218 --> 45:20.927
Excuse me?
Have we met somewhere?

45:20.928 --> 45:22.721
I don't think so.

45:23.472 --> 45:25.891
She looked at me first.

45:28.685 --> 45:30.812
Sit down.
Thank you.

45:44.868 --> 45:47.120
You okay?
I'm fine.

45:47.496 --> 45:50.207
I was going to call you today.

45:54.419 --> 45:59.341
I... This is
terribly embarrassing.

45:59.675 --> 46:04.220
I just wanted to say sorry
for what happened.

46:04.221 --> 46:07.349
I had no right to put
you through all that.

46:10.018 --> 46:12.103
Nothing happened, okay?

46:12.104 --> 46:14.021
I was going through a bad time.

46:14.022 --> 46:16.857
And everything was coming
to a crisis, and...

46:16.858 --> 46:20.821
But I'm fine.
I'm really all right.
And thank you.

46:21.446 --> 46:23.114
You don't have to thank me.

46:23.115 --> 46:24.532
Oh, yeah, I do.

46:24.533 --> 46:27.618
A lot of guys would
have just run away.

46:27.619 --> 46:31.707
I don't know what
I would have done
if you hadn't been there.

46:32.207 --> 46:37.713
Well, you look good.
As a matter of fact,
you look great.

46:38.922 --> 46:40.382
Thanks.

46:42.801 --> 46:44.845
So that's past?

46:45.387 --> 46:46.722
Yeah.

46:49.016 --> 46:50.850
May I ask you one more favor?

46:50.851 --> 46:52.519
What's that?

46:53.645 --> 46:59.151
I've got two tickets
to <i>Madame Butterfly,</i>
two weeks from Thursday.

47:00.110 --> 47:05.240
I'd really love it
if you'd come with me,
kind of as a peace offering.

47:05.824 --> 47:08.577
Well, that's very nice of you.

47:10.579 --> 47:12.788
But I don't think
it's a good idea.

47:12.789 --> 47:14.207
No strings attached.

47:14.750 --> 47:15.500
Alex.

47:15.501 --> 47:19.546
I know,
you don't have to explain.
I just thought I'd ask.

47:22.132 --> 47:23.383
So...

47:27.346 --> 47:30.057
I'll see you around sometime.

47:31.516 --> 47:32.768
Okay.

47:46.656 --> 47:48.200
Come here.

47:53.372 --> 47:54.580
Take care.

47:54.581 --> 47:56.083
Yeah. Goodbye.

47:56.792 --> 47:58.293
Goodbye.

48:04.800 --> 48:07.219
[OPERA MUSIC PLAYING]

48:25.987 --> 48:28.781
All right.
Come on, let's go, pal.

48:28.782 --> 48:31.910
We're on a roll.
We're on a roll.

48:34.371 --> 48:35.788
DAN: Let's see that action.

48:35.789 --> 48:36.914
Down the middle.

48:36.915 --> 48:38.834
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

48:40.419 --> 48:42.295
I like it. Very nice.

48:42.671 --> 48:45.298
[OPERA MUSIC PLAYING]

48:56.268 --> 48:57.978
[ALL CHEERING]

49:00.522 --> 49:03.233
HILDY: That is no good.
I'm depressed.

49:31.219 --> 49:34.054
What about Rodgers v.whatchamacallit?

49:34.055 --> 49:35.056
Winitsky.
Right.

49:35.057 --> 49:38.184
I got your memo.
You're going to
go for summary judgment?

49:38.185 --> 49:40.603
Why not, Arthur?
I mean, the facts
are not in dispute.

49:40.604 --> 49:42.688
Rodgers admits
reading Winitsky's article.

49:42.689 --> 49:45.566
The question is whether
he plagiarized it in his book.

49:45.567 --> 49:47.443
As you know,
you can't copyright an idea,

49:47.444 --> 49:48.652
only the expression of the idea,

49:48.653 --> 49:52.823
and Rodgers sure as hell
didn't use any of the words
in the book.

49:52.824 --> 49:54.742
Let me think about it.
Okay.

49:54.743 --> 49:57.161
So I hear you're about to
become a suburbanite.

49:57.162 --> 49:59.246
Yeah, we're gonna
take the big plunge.

49:59.247 --> 50:00.831
Got a buyer for the apartment?

50:00.832 --> 50:01.833
No.

50:01.834 --> 50:03.709
Got cold sweats
about your escrow?

50:03.710 --> 50:05.127
Yeah.

50:05.128 --> 50:07.880
But not about Rodgers vs.
Winitsky?

50:07.881 --> 50:09.758
No, sir.
Good.

50:10.258 --> 50:12.594
He's still in a meeting.

50:12.928 --> 50:17.098
Yes, I know.
I did expect him to
be through by now.

50:20.268 --> 50:22.645
I'd like you to have
lunch with me on Tuesday,
if you're around.

50:22.646 --> 50:25.689
Well, thank you, Arthur,
that'd be great. Let me
just check my diary.

50:25.690 --> 50:28.817
You are on his list of calls.
It's Alex Forrest.

50:28.818 --> 50:32.696
Again? I thought you told her
I'd call her back.

50:32.697 --> 50:34.532
I did.
All right.
Put her on hold.

50:34.533 --> 50:36.617
Would you mind holding?
He'll be free in a moment.

50:36.618 --> 50:38.203
Tuesday would be great, Arthur.

50:38.286 --> 50:41.164
I look forward to it.
Thank you. I will, too.

50:44.084 --> 50:45.335
Put her through.

50:52.467 --> 50:53.802
Hello?

50:54.177 --> 50:58.431
Look,
Alex, I thought we agreed
this was not a good idea.

51:01.184 --> 51:02.644
Why?

51:06.481 --> 51:08.357
Look, I'm sorry.
I thought you understood.

51:08.358 --> 51:11.318
If I've misled you
in some way, I apologize.

51:11.319 --> 51:15.322
But I don't think it's
a good idea if we talk
to each other anymore.

51:15.323 --> 51:16.658
Okay?

51:18.326 --> 51:19.619
Goodbye.

51:25.750 --> 51:30.046
Yeah, if she calls again,
tell her I'm not here.
Thank you.

52:15.592 --> 52:17.468
Wait, let me just...

52:17.469 --> 52:19.804
Let me just look at you.

52:21.765 --> 52:23.850
You're so beautiful.

52:24.476 --> 52:26.561
Just so beautiful.

52:35.487 --> 52:36.988
[DOORBELL RINGING]

52:39.741 --> 52:42.243
Wouldn't you know?
I know.

52:48.083 --> 52:50.668
DAN: Open it, will you?
That's my wife!

52:50.669 --> 52:53.379
JIMMY: I wouldn't do it
to my wife.

52:53.380 --> 52:54.630
BETH: You know what?
It's okay.

52:54.631 --> 52:56.840
You don't know how many
injuries can happen?

52:56.841 --> 52:59.176
It's my wife
he's doing it...
Jimmy, don't terrorize them!

52:59.177 --> 53:03.181
I'm a lawyer, I'm insured.
Oh, it's excited.

53:03.348 --> 53:05.474
Now, don't forget
who gave you this,
all right?

53:05.475 --> 53:08.060
My cold sores
are almost gone.
This is for you.

53:08.061 --> 53:11.439
Ladies first.
I use that term advisedly.

53:12.440 --> 53:14.233
You're the best.

53:14.234 --> 53:16.568
That's my wife!
All right, ladies...

53:16.569 --> 53:18.737
A little attention,
please, ladies.

53:18.738 --> 53:23.451
Gentlemen,
my wife, ball and chain.

53:24.202 --> 53:25.786
Mother of some of my children.

53:25.787 --> 53:27.162
I wouldn't be that
confident about it.
Absolutely.

53:27.163 --> 53:33.127
Here is to Miller, Goodman,
Hurst and Gallagher!

53:33.128 --> 53:34.586
And to Mrs. Gallagher.

53:34.587 --> 53:35.921
Give me a break, will you, guys?

53:35.922 --> 53:37.297
All he did is ask me
to lunch, you know?

53:37.298 --> 53:39.341
Yeah, and you're moving
to your country estate.

53:39.342 --> 53:40.467
You'll forget you
never knew us plebs.

53:40.468 --> 53:43.679
Oh, no, wait a minute.
I read one of
those self-help books.

53:43.680 --> 53:45.389
Published by Robbins & Hart, of course.

53:45.390 --> 53:48.643
Of course.
<i>Samurai Self-Help.</i>

53:49.018 --> 53:50.937
[BOTH EXCLAIMING]

53:53.022 --> 53:57.484
In it, it tells you how
to deal with the anxieties
of your friends

53:57.485 --> 53:59.737
as you move up
the corporate ladder

53:59.738 --> 54:01.905
and they stay put,
or God forbid, go down.

54:01.906 --> 54:04.116
And in this book, it tells you

54:04.117 --> 54:06.535
not to coddle your
friends' anxieties.

54:06.536 --> 54:09.413
So, I'm not gonna make
any false reassurances, guys.

54:09.414 --> 54:11.832
I'm not gonna tell you
you're gonna be at the
house every weekend.

54:11.833 --> 54:13.876
I mean, let's face it.
Things have changed.

54:13.877 --> 54:16.628
This is not a classless society.

54:16.629 --> 54:20.132
As a matter of fact,
this is it, guys.
Goodbye. Goodbye.

54:20.133 --> 54:22.134
I knew he was gonna say that!

54:22.135 --> 54:23.594
At least the man is
running true to form.

54:23.595 --> 54:25.137
Honey, I think we got to
make a clean break.

54:25.138 --> 54:27.931
I mean, we're on a roll.
We got to travel light.
Let's face it.

54:27.932 --> 54:28.892
[PHONE RINGING]

54:28.892 --> 54:29.851
Travel light. Exactly.
Absolutely.

54:29.852 --> 54:33.354
Thanks for the time
you've given us in your lives.

54:34.439 --> 54:36.441
[RINGING CONTINUES]

54:38.693 --> 54:39.818
JIMMY: Here you, drink.

54:39.819 --> 54:41.612
I want you with a lampshade
on your head by 10:00.

54:41.613 --> 54:45.533
Why should today
be any different,
you know what I mean?

54:46.618 --> 54:49.537
Hello? Hello?

54:50.914 --> 54:53.541
JIMMY: [LAUGHING]
Here's to you.

54:54.918 --> 54:56.211
Cheers.

54:59.255 --> 55:00.548
Hello?

55:02.801 --> 55:04.177
Hello!

55:34.916 --> 55:37.085
[PHONE RINGING]

55:43.216 --> 55:44.551
Yeah?

55:48.930 --> 55:52.559
Yeah, Richards.
It's kind of late, isn't it?

55:53.852 --> 55:55.227
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

55:55.228 --> 55:57.729
If you refuse to
take my phone calls
at the office,

55:57.730 --> 55:59.606
you leave me no choice.

55:59.607 --> 56:04.278
It's 2:00 in the morning
here. Can't this wait
till tomorrow morning?

56:04.279 --> 56:06.614
Oh, is it awkward
for you to talk?

56:08.157 --> 56:10.577
You could say that, yeah.

56:11.578 --> 56:13.537
I've got to see you.

56:13.538 --> 56:18.250
I don't have the
documentation to answer
that question right now,

56:18.251 --> 56:20.502
but I'll call you
from the office.

56:20.503 --> 56:25.466
No. Meet me in front of the Robbins & Hart
building tomorrow. 6:00.

56:25.925 --> 56:29.929
Don't disappoint me.
Be there.

56:31.222 --> 56:32.473
Okay.

56:37.228 --> 56:37.979
This has got to stop.

56:37.980 --> 56:40.272
Dan,
if you'd agreed to see me,
I wouldn't have called you.

56:40.273 --> 56:43.108
Do you get it,
all right? It's over.
There is nothing between us.

56:43.109 --> 56:44.359
You've mean you've had your fun,

56:44.360 --> 56:46.446
now you just want a quiet life.

56:46.696 --> 56:48.488
Why are you doing this?
Doing what?

56:48.489 --> 56:49.324
You need help.

56:49.325 --> 56:52.367
Don't tell me
what I need.
You need a shrink.

56:52.368 --> 56:54.578
Why are you so hostile?
I'm not your enemy.

56:54.579 --> 56:55.913
Yeah, then why are you
trying to hurt me?

56:55.914 --> 56:58.582
I'm not trying
to hurt you, Dan.
I love you.

56:58.583 --> 57:00.710
You what?
I love you.

57:02.545 --> 57:04.546
You don't even know me.
Oh, how can you say that?

57:04.547 --> 57:07.049
Alex, we spent a weekend
together, that's all.

57:07.050 --> 57:09.176
You spent that second night.
You must like me a little.

57:09.177 --> 57:11.386
Because I was
concerned about you.
Jesus Christ!

57:11.387 --> 57:12.930
Why do you read so much
into everything?

57:12.931 --> 57:14.473
I mean, can't you understand?

57:14.474 --> 57:17.100
I have a whole relationship
with someone else.

57:17.101 --> 57:18.644
I am very happy.

57:18.645 --> 57:19.978
Whole means complete.

57:19.979 --> 57:22.606
If your life's so
damn complete, what were
you doing with me?

57:22.607 --> 57:25.734
Is this what you
want to talk about,
our imaginary love affair?

57:25.735 --> 57:27.445
I'm pregnant.

57:31.324 --> 57:34.326
I saw my gynecologist on Monday.

57:34.327 --> 57:36.913
Here's his card.
You can call him.

57:43.836 --> 57:45.505
You don't...

57:47.173 --> 57:49.342
Use anything? No.

57:49.926 --> 57:51.843
I had a very bad
miscarriage last year.

57:51.844 --> 57:54.555
I didn't think
I could get pregnant.

57:55.848 --> 57:57.892
And how do you know it's mine?

58:00.728 --> 58:03.398
Because I don't sleep around.

58:14.659 --> 58:16.452
I apologize.

58:18.579 --> 58:20.372
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

58:20.373 --> 58:23.583
Don't worry, all right?
You're not going to have
to handle this alone.

58:23.584 --> 58:25.294
Handle what?

58:25.503 --> 58:29.590
The abortion.
I'll take care of it.
I'll pay for it.

58:30.133 --> 58:32.719
What makes you think
I want an abortion?

58:36.723 --> 58:38.598
You're not going
to have the baby?

58:38.599 --> 58:40.268
Why not?

58:40.852 --> 58:43.270
There are plenty of
one-parent families.

58:43.271 --> 58:45.313
At least they don't
end in divorce.

58:45.314 --> 58:47.065
I don't have a say in this?

58:47.066 --> 58:51.903
I want this child.
It has nothing
to do with you.

58:51.904 --> 58:54.281
I want it whether
you're going to be
a part of it or not.

58:54.282 --> 58:55.907
Then why are you
telling me? Why?

58:55.908 --> 58:58.202
Why not just go ahead and do it?

59:01.080 --> 59:03.915
I was hoping that
you would want to be
a part of it.

59:03.916 --> 59:08.462
This is crazy.
This is totally insane.

59:08.463 --> 59:12.049
I'm 36 years old.
It may be my last chance
to have a child.

59:12.050 --> 59:13.342
Alex...

59:15.511 --> 59:18.306
Just think what you're saying.

59:19.098 --> 59:21.183
Just think about it.

59:21.184 --> 59:25.813
We are going to live with this
for the rest of our lives.

59:26.689 --> 59:28.483
I know that.

59:29.067 --> 59:33.320
I've thought of that.
I know how you feel.
It's a big thing.

59:33.321 --> 59:37.616
But it doesn't have
to be a problem.
Really, it doesn't.

59:37.617 --> 59:41.454
You play fair with me,
I'll play fair with you.

59:46.918 --> 59:50.545
BETH: "He led Agnes
and Nellie into the hall
closet and shut the door.

59:50.546 --> 59:54.091
"Agnes and Nellie
and Oink giggled and
laughed in the dark.

59:54.092 --> 59:58.095
"Pearl listened
outside the door.
'Oh, it works, ' cried Nellie.

59:58.096 --> 01:00:02.099
"'Of course, ' said Oink.
'Look at the flying
dog!' yelled Agnes.

01:00:02.100 --> 01:00:03.517
"'Wow, ' cried Nellie.

01:00:03.518 --> 01:00:07.437
"Pearl frowned. 'Who cares
about flying dogs?' she said.

01:00:07.438 --> 01:00:08.980
"Nobody heard her.

01:00:08.981 --> 01:00:11.399
"'Look out for the worms!'
squealed Agnes.

01:00:11.400 --> 01:00:13.985
"'Eek!' yelled
Nellie and Agnes together.

01:00:13.986 --> 01:00:19.826
"'Look at the monster
cockroach!' yelled Oink.
'Ick! Help!'"

01:00:59.157 --> 01:01:00.658
[DOOR BUZZING]

01:03:01.487 --> 01:03:03.905
So, you know what I did?
Right.

01:03:03.906 --> 01:03:04.907
I call the doctor.

01:03:04.908 --> 01:03:07.660
And you know what he says?
"Congratulations!"

01:03:08.202 --> 01:03:11.121
I can't even imagine
what she told him.

01:03:11.122 --> 01:03:14.457
Anyway, that's not
the end of it.

01:03:14.458 --> 01:03:16.751
So, after I talked
to the doctor,

01:03:16.752 --> 01:03:20.631
this morning,
I broke into her apartment.

01:03:20.756 --> 01:03:23.633
I know. Me, a lawyer,
breaking and entering.

01:03:23.634 --> 01:03:24.719
I don't know,
I'm looking for something,

01:03:24.720 --> 01:03:26.636
anything to get a handle on
what I'm dealing with here.

01:03:26.637 --> 01:03:28.513
I thought maybe if
I can find out she was

01:03:28.514 --> 01:03:31.182
sleeping with
somebody else, you know.

01:03:31.183 --> 01:03:32.434
I didn't find anything.

01:03:32.435 --> 01:03:34.020
[SQUEAKING]

01:03:37.773 --> 01:03:40.526
Anyway, I didn't find anything.

01:03:42.236 --> 01:03:43.695
Jimmy, I don't know.
I don't know

01:03:43.696 --> 01:03:45.196
anything about family law, okay?

01:03:45.197 --> 01:03:46.740
So you gotta help me now.

01:03:46.741 --> 01:03:49.201
What kind of case
does she really have?

01:03:52.330 --> 01:03:54.457
Well, it ain't good.

01:03:56.709 --> 01:03:59.670
She keeps calling the apartment.

01:04:00.254 --> 01:04:04.175
Every time Beth
answers the phone,
she hangs up.

01:04:05.718 --> 01:04:08.054
I'm scared, Jimmy. I...

01:04:08.888 --> 01:04:11.807
I don't want to lose my family.

01:04:17.646 --> 01:04:22.192
<i>The facts as alleged
are horrendous.</i>

01:04:22.193 --> 01:04:25.028
MAN: [ON TV] <i>The instrument allegedly used</i>
<i>in all three cases</i>

01:04:25.029 --> 01:04:26.321
<i>was an electronic shock device,</i>

01:04:26.322 --> 01:04:30.575
<i>or stun gun, now</i>
<i>standard issue for</i>
<i>New York City police.</i>

01:04:30.576 --> 01:04:33.244
The stun guns, which jolt and incapacitate the body

01:04:33.245 --> 01:04:36.414
<i>by interrupting</i>
<i>electrical waves</i>
<i>to the muscles,</i>

01:04:36.415 --> 01:04:40.502
are being used or experimented with by 500 police agencies

01:04:40.503 --> 01:04:41.545
<i>across the country,</i>

01:04:41.546 --> 01:04:45.257
marketed as an alternative to the nightsticks.

01:04:45.508 --> 01:04:46.633
MAN: [ON PHONE] Operator, may I help you?

01:04:46.634 --> 01:04:51.513
Operator, I've been
trying to get
555-812-9212.

01:04:51.514 --> 01:04:53.598
The recording says
it's been disconnected.

01:04:53.599 --> 01:04:55.934
Just a moment, please.

01:04:55.935 --> 01:04:58.269
<i>I'm sorry. The number's been changed to an unlisted number.</i>

01:04:58.270 --> 01:04:59.646
Operator,
this is a real emergency.

01:04:59.647 --> 01:05:00.855
Please, you need to
give me that number.

01:05:00.856 --> 01:05:03.400
<i>I'm sorry, we're not allowed to give out that information.</i>

01:05:03.401 --> 01:05:04.859
Well, fuck you!

01:05:04.860 --> 01:05:06.487
Oh, my place or yours?

01:05:16.080 --> 01:05:17.665
[CAR HORN BLARING]

01:05:43.482 --> 01:05:45.733
ALEX: I like it.
I like it a lot.

01:05:45.734 --> 01:05:47.318
BETH: Well,
we've been very happy here.

01:05:47.319 --> 01:05:51.198
ALEX: I'd definitely like
to think about it if I could.

01:05:51.866 --> 01:05:54.367
...to clean and all?
BETH: Yes.

01:05:54.368 --> 01:05:55.577
I have a lady that comes in

01:05:55.578 --> 01:05:58.037
a couple times a week,
as a matter of fact.

01:05:58.038 --> 01:06:00.331
And I can certainly give
you her name as well.

01:06:00.332 --> 01:06:01.167
ALEX: Oh, I'd love that.

01:06:01.168 --> 01:06:04.294
BETH: And I have
babysitters galore.
The whole works.

01:06:04.295 --> 01:06:07.256
Whatever information
you would need.

01:06:11.302 --> 01:06:13.928
Hi, darling.
Darling, this is Alex.

01:06:13.929 --> 01:06:15.555
I'm sorry, I've
forgotten your last name.

01:06:15.556 --> 01:06:19.643
Alex Forrest.
Alex Forrest,
this is my husband Dan.

01:06:21.270 --> 01:06:23.647
Hi. Glad to meet you.

01:06:25.774 --> 01:06:27.735
Nice to meet you.

01:06:29.111 --> 01:06:31.362
Haven't we met somewhere before?

01:06:31.363 --> 01:06:33.032
I don't think so. No.

01:06:36.827 --> 01:06:40.163
No, we have.
Weren't you at that party

01:06:40.164 --> 01:06:42.540
at the Japanese place,
a few weeks ago?

01:06:42.541 --> 01:06:44.709
Honey, the exercise book.

